        primaryText: 'For 8 years, I was told I had to choose: safe or scented. Never both.\n\nMultiple Chemical Sensitivity took fragrance from me the way a thief takes something in the night \u2014 slowly, then all at once. First it was perfume. Then scented lotion. Then candles. Then laundry detergent. One by one, every beautiful scent in my life became a weapon against my own body.\n\nI switched to free and clear everything. My migraines decreased. My breathing stabilized. But I lost something nobody talks about: the simple pleasure of pulling warm laundry from the dryer and inhaling something beautiful.\n\nI grieved that. Silently. For years.\n\nThen I found Maison Laundrin. And I need to explain WHY it\'s different, because if you have MCS, you\'ve heard \'safe and scented\' before and it was a lie.\n\nMaison Laundrin uses micro-encapsulation technology. The fragrance is sealed inside plant-based capsules. They don\'t off-gas. They don\'t release volatile organic compounds into the air. The scent is released ONLY through mechanical friction \u2014 when fabric moves against itself or your skin.\n\nThis is not traditional fragrance delivered gently. This is a fundamentally different delivery mechanism.\n\nI washed one load. I held my breath. I waited for the migraine. It didn\'t come. I smelled the shirt. Peach blossom and vanilla. Beautiful. And my body didn\'t punish me for it.\n\nI sat on my laundry room floor and cried.\n\nFor the first time in 8 years, I smelled beautiful. And I could breathe.',
