        primaryText: 'She posted in our MCS support group at 2 AM: \'I found something. And I can breathe.\'\n\nWe\'ve all seen those posts before. Someone finds a \'natural\' detergent. They\'re excited for a week. Then the delayed reaction hits. The migraine. The respiratory flare. The crash.\n\nSo we were skeptical. All of us.\n\nBut she explained the science. Micro-encapsulated fragrance. Not traditional scent that evaporates into the air as VOCs. Fragrance sealed inside plant-based capsules that only release through physical friction. No off-gassing. No airborne compounds.\n\nThree of us tried it. Then five. Then eleven.\n\nNobody reacted.\n\nLet me say that again: NOBODY reacted.\n\nNot the woman with MCS so severe she can\'t enter a grocery store. Not the woman whose fibromyalgia makes every fabric feel like sandpaper. Not the woman who hasn\'t worn anything scented in twelve years.\n\nMaison Laundrin didn\'t cure our conditions. Nothing will. But it gave us back something we\'d been grieving: the simple pleasure of clothes that smell beautiful.\n\nAnd we can breathe.',
