        primaryText: 'My clothes hurt. That sounds impossible unless you have fibromyalgia.\n\nTactile allodynia. The medical term for when normal touch becomes pain. Seams feel like wire. Tags feel like blades. And chemical residue from harsh detergents turns every piece of clothing into low-grade sandpaper against hypersensitive skin.\n\nI\'ve tried every free and clear detergent. They help with the chemical residue. But they leave fabric stiff. And they strip any possibility of scent \u2014 the one sensory pleasure that might actually comfort me.\n\nMaison Laundrin is different in two ways that matter for fibromyalgia:\n\nFirst, the enzyme system breaks down residue at the molecular level. No SLS. No optical brighteners. No synthetic compounds clinging to fibers. Fabric comes out genuinely clean and soft \u2014 not chemically coated in \'softness.\'\n\nSecond, the micro-encapsulated fragrance doesn\'t contact skin directly. The capsules are embedded in the fabric and release scent through movement and friction. Your skin touches clean, soft fabric. The scent comes from the fabric itself, not from chemicals sitting on the surface.\n\nFor the first time, I pulled on a shirt and felt two things simultaneously: comfort and beauty.\n\nMy clothes don\'t hurt anymore. And they smell like peach blossom and vanilla.\n\nI didn\'t know I was allowed to have both.',
