        hook: 'I haven\'t smelled beautiful in six years. Today I do.',
        primaryText: 'I haven\'t smelled beautiful in six years. Today I do.\n\nSix years ago, Multiple Chemical Sensitivity took scent from my life. Not gradually \u2014 violently. A migraine from laundry detergent that lasted four days. Respiratory distress from a coworker\'s fabric softener. Nausea from sitting in a chair someone had sprayed with Febreze.\n\nI eliminated everything. Free and clear detergent. Fragrance-free soap. Unscented everything. My world became clinically safe and sensorially dead.\n\nI adapted. But I never stopped missing it. The warmth of vanilla on a sweater. The freshness of clean linen on sheets. The moment you pull something from the dryer and it smells like comfort.\n\nI mourned those moments quietly.\n\nMaison Laundrin uses micro-encapsulation \u2014 fragrance sealed in plant-based capsules that don\'t off-gas, don\'t release VOCs, and don\'t evaporate into the air. They release ONLY through friction. Movement. The gentle motion of wearing your clothes.\n\nNo SLS. No phthalates. No methylisothiazolinone. No optical brighteners.\n\nI washed a single pillowcase. I held it to my face. Luxe Blanc \u2014 clean, luminous, gentle.\n\nAnd I could breathe.\n\nI smelled beautiful. And nothing hurt.\n\nI\'m not cured. MCS doesn\'t work that way. But for the first time in six years, I have something I thought was gone forever: the pleasure of scent without the punishment.\n\nThat\'s not a product benefit. That\'s a piece of my life returned.',
